      "title": "Three faces of -ed",
      "body": "English spells the past tense “-ed”, but says it three different ways — and Shavian writes what you say. First: say “jumped”. Hear the t at the end? So it’s written 𐑑: 𐑡𐑳𐑥𐑐𐑑."
